# IH design system — always in Agent context (compact)

Designers should not need to re‑teach the basics every session. **Always include** the compact core below so the Agent knows **what the IH design system is**, **how to layer sources**, and **when to open the full spec**.

**Included file:**

@design-sandbox/DESIGN_AGENT_CORE.md

**Behavior**

- Treat **`design-sandbox/design.md`** as the **full written source of truth** for tables, per‑component rules, messaging detail, patterns, and curated Figma links—**read it when the task needs that depth** (see the “When to open” section inside **`DESIGN_AGENT_CORE.md`**).
- Use **Figma MCP** / **ih-figma-ds-visual-refs** for Anatomy visuals, variants, and Code Connect when implementation fidelity matters.
- Use **`design-sandbox/app-visual-language.md`** and **`design-sandbox/personas/`** for product‑specific overlay.
